msgctxt "talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Who are you?!<2.pa> Be on your way, you...\n"
"suspicious man!<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Huh? <2.pa>I've seen that <3.se_co>blue flame<4.re_co> before.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"I'd see that old woman Purah<5.pa> carrying it\n"
"up to her place all the time..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That <2.se_co>blue flame<3.re_co> <4.se_co><5.pa><6.re_co>is for "
"Purah, right?<7.pa>\n"
"Then stop wasting time chatting with me\n"
"and deliver it! Quickly."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: sound
#. 6: set_colour (blue)
#. 7: reset_colour
#. 8: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Huh? <2.pa>I've seen that <3.se_co>blue flame<4.re_co> before.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>I used to see the <6.se_co>director of the \n"
"research facility<7.re_co><8.pa> carrying it up the hill\n"
"all the time."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: set_colour (blue)
#. 8: reset_colour
#. 9: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That <2.se_co>blue flame<3.re_co> <4.se_co><5.pa><6.re_co>is for "
"the <7.se_co>director<8.re_co>, right?<9.pa>\n"
"Then stop yapping with me and deliver it\n"
"quickly!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: set_colour (blue)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk07"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You're free to go.<2.pa> We're just a waypoint\n"
"on your winding road, huh? \n"
"\n"
"Ah, the life of a traveler. Well, you can\n"
"get most things you need at the <3.se_co>general\n"
"store<4.re_co>,<5.pa> and the<6.se_co> inn<7.re_co> is just back there."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid "<1.so>Phwaaa... <2.pa>So sleepy."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid "<1.so>You still need something?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid "<1.so>Wha? <2.pa>Oh, it's you...<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid "<1.so>Go on, then."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: sound
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: sound
#. 7: sound
#. 8: pause (short)
#. 9: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Not likely!<2.pa> I'm on guard duty, Buster!\n"
"Serious business! No time for tours!<3.pa>\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>Grumble...<5.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<6.so>Sorry for the yelling...and the grumbling.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<7.so>This village is pretty peaceful, so it's not\n"
"like guard duty is all that harrowing.\n"
"\n"
"But you're GRAVELY mistaken if you \n"
"think people with free time are itching to\n"
"give village tours.<8.pa>\n"
"Try looking for a burly old guy called\n"
"Seldon.<9.pa> He'll probably fall all over\n"
"himself to show you around."
msgstr ""

