msgctxt "talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>This is the town of greenery and dyes, \n"
"Hateno Village.\n"
"\n"
"<2.se_co><3.te_si>Can a place be a village AND a town?<4.pa> "
"Anyway...<5.te_si><6.re_co>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"The vegetables taste good. The air smells\n"
"good...<7.pa> What else... All kinds of points\n"
"of interest I'm forgetting...\n"
"Travelers tend to spend their money\n"
"here,<8.pa> so that's good! Yeah! The village\n"
"folk welcome THAT with open arms!\n"
"<9.te_si>But...<10.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Who... Who are you?! I demand answers!<2.pa>\n"
"If you're up this late, you're probably\n"
"up to no good!<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid "<1.so>Wait, wait, wait!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hrm? \n"
"\n"
"\n"
"You certainly do appear to be a <2.se_co>Hylian<3.re_co>\n"
"like the rest of us..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.se_co>Hylians<3.re_co> are generally good folk, so...<4.pa>\n"
"Sorry for getting all worked up..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (long)
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>A little advice? Don't go near the <2.se_co>place\n"
"up the hill in the rear of the village<3.re_co>.<4.pa>\n"
"There's a yappy <5.se_co>old woman<6.re_co> there."
msgstr ""

